post_text:
A huge shout out to our Jubilee-Brownsville graduates! We look forward to celebrating them on June 19th.

Our Titan highlights truly do speak for themselves:

Valedictorian, Noah Barnard, who will be graduating with his Diploma and Associate Degree, attending SMU in the Fall, is a proud Gates & Hunt Scholar. Noah is also the 1st charter school student to receive the Gates Scholarship.

Maria Lozano played varsity volleyball, was a Member of the National Honor Society and an ambassador. She has enrolled in Southern Careers Institute where she will start on June 15th and within 5 weeks will receive her CNA. Later, she will be attending Texas A&M University-Corpus Christi where she will be pursuing her nursing degree while working as a CNA.

Jose Salas has been part of Jubilee Academies since it opened in Brownsville. He was a Cross Country runner for the past 7 years and has now enlisted with the U.S. Marine Corps.

post_text:
We are proud to announce and congratulate our first CTE dual credit student who earned industry-based certifications this year. Kenneth Martinez, a student at Jubilee - San Antonio, completed his junior year with the Alamo Academies-Advanced Technology and Manufacturing Academy.

He successfully completed his first year in the academy and earned the following certifications:

1. Manufacturing Skill Standards Council (MSSC) Safety Certification
2. OSHA 10-Hour Certification
3. Level 1 Certificate-Industrial Maintenance Assistant

We are proud of our CTE students, and look forward to working with them in preparation for high-skill, high-wage, and in-demand occupations through our dual credit partnerships and campus based programs of study.

Join us as we celebrate #GivingTuesdayNow! In response to the need caused by COVID-19, AmplifyAustin has generously offered $10,000 in incentive funds for donations made to nonprofit organizations like Jubilee Wells Branch on Tuesday, May 5th, 2020.

AmplifyAustin will also randomly select 20 donors over the 24-hour #GivingTuesdayNow period to give $250 each to the nonprofit of their choice. Jubilee Wells Branch will be utilizing the funds gathered during #GivingTuesdayNow towards our summer school and distance learning initiatives, such as providing hotspots for internet, distributing meals and offering relief for families who need financial assistance.

Now's your chance to show your Jubilee Spirit. Go to https://bit.ly/GivingJubilee to donate now!

Starting this week, we will be expanding our meal distribution to include Jubilee-Brownsville, Jubilee-Westwood, & Jubilee-Wells Branch. We will offer 5 days of breakfast and lunch meals, which will be available to all children 18 years and under. Children do not need to attend Jubilee Academies or be present at pick up to receive a meal as long as parents provide one of the following required documents:

> Official letter/email from school that shows enrollment>
> Individual student report cards
> Attendance record from Parent Portal or school website
> Birth certificate for children not in school
> Student ID cards
**No documentation is necessary if the child is present

In an effort to ensure that we are abiding by our mission “To provide a nurturing community focused on leadership and
educational excellence,” we will once again distribute free meals to families that attend our schools as well as any other families in our community that may have a need. We will offer 5 days of breakfast and lunch meals, which will be available to all children 18 years and under.

Children do not need to attend Jubilee Academies or be present at pick up to receive a meal as long as parents provide one of the following required documents:

• Official letter/email from school that shows children as enrolled
• Individual student report cards
• Attendance record from Parent Portal or school website
• Birth certificate for children not in school
• Student ID cards
**No documentation is necessary if the child is present

The virus lives in tiny droplets in the lungs of people w/ COVID-19, even when they don’t show symptoms. We can breathe the same air as anyone within abt. 6 ft. of us. Staying farther apart from people during this time reduces the chance of breathing in the virus. #StayHomeTexas

El virus vive en gotas en los pulmones de personas con COVID-19, y a veces no tienen síntomas. Puedes respirar el mismo aire que cualquiera a 6 pies de ti. Mantente más alejado de las personas durante este tiempo para reducir la posibilidad de respirar el virus. #StayHomeTexas

Coughing & sneezing can send tiny infected droplets into the air which can be inhaled by anyone within 6 feet of us. Always cough or sneeze into a tissue or your elbow and immediately wash your hands to lessen the risk of spreading the virus. Be smart. Stay well! #StayHomeTexas

Toser y estornudar puede llevar gotas infectadas al aire, que pueden ser inhaladas por personas que estén a 6 pies de ti. Siempre tosa o estornude en pañuelos desechables o en el codo y lávese las manos para disminuir la propagación del virus. ¡Mantente sano! #StayHomeTexas

In order to help prevent the spread of COVID-19, Jubilee Academies’ LAST DAY to serve grab and go meals is TODAY April 6th. The meals will be served from 11:30 am-1:00 pm and will be available for curbside pick-up at the five sites. Multiple days of breakfast and lunch food will be served. In an additional effort to keep our families safe, we have CANCELLED distribution for our Jubilee - Kingsville and Jubilee - San Antonio locations.

We know this is a difficult time and we care about you. Listed below are some resources to help families in need find food in every region.

Thank you all for your patience and understanding as we move through these trying times together.

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Los síntomas comunes de #COVID19 son fiebre, tos seca y dificultad para respirar.Si tiene síntomas leves, llame a su médico y quedate en casa.Si desarrolla síntomas graves, como dificultad para respirar o presión en el pecho, busque atención médica de inmediato. #StayHome

Meals will be shelf stable and only available TODAY. The organization is working on a plan to serve meals at more of our schools in the future.

Jubilee Academies will continue serving breakfast and lunch meals for pick-up at the same time. Children must be present to receive these meals.

post_text:
Jubilee Academies has decided to extend closure so that classes on campus will tentatively resume Monday, April 27, 2020. Distribution of instructional packets and meal services will continue as scheduled.

Please remember participation in distance and
online learning where offered is required for all students. If you have not heard from your teachers, please reach out to them and the campus administrators.

If you are in the San Antonio and Kingsville Regions and have not picked up a device from the campus, please contact the campus administrative team via email. The RGV and Austin Regions will be issuing devices within the next few days.

To stay up-to-date on updates and resources, please visit the district website: www.jubileeacademies.org

Today a few of our Jubilee-Brownsville students who are also involved in Girl Scouts and Boy Scouts of America were invited to participate in the 68th Annual Scouts Government Day held by the City of Brownsville, TX - Municipal Government. The event allows students to be selected for a currently held city government or city department position and invited to shadow the community and city leaders in their daily roles.

At the end of the day, each elected student representative will report to the Mayor and City Commissioners on their experience and findings.

Congratulations to all the students invited and thank you to the City of Brownsville for the opportunity.

#riseup #standstrong #gameon

post_text:
Jubilee Academies is pleased to introduce a new communications tool called Anonymous Alerts.

The Anonymous Alerts anti-bullying and safety app reporting system helps combat bullying and other negative activity in schools by empowering students to speak up. Social and peer pressure are some of the hardest obstacles for students to overcome.

The system allows for 1-way or 2-way anonymous encrypted communications between submitters (students, parents or community members) and district administration and/or school staff. Users of the system have the option to remain anonymous or reveal their identity when submitting a report.

Learn more on our website:
http://bit.ly/34WoFvz

Very early this morning Jubilee - Kingsville staff and students participated in the 32nd Annual Share your Christmas live broadcast at KIII-TV studios.
Together, they collected 1800 lbs of food. 2,065 cans!
shared_text:
Jubilee - Kingsville
December 6, 2019 at 7:58 AM ·

Very early this morning Jubilee-Kingsville staff and students participated in the 32nd Annual Share your Christmas live broadcast at KIII-TV studios.

Jubilee-Kingsville started collecting canned goods and monetary donations to benefit the Coastal Bend Food Bank. We collected 1800 lbs of food. 2,065 cans.

Beyond giving back to the community, students and schools that collect the highest pound per student are eligible to receive a Grand Prize for their school! More details and images will follow. Results will be announced later today.

A huge shout out and Thank You to Mr. Steve Marquez Solis, Associate Superintendent, Mr Joey Acevedo, Principal, the incredible school staff members and most importantly, the parents and students at Jubilee-Kingsville who made this event successful and who truly Shared their Christmas with those in need.

This is the true meaning of the holidays.

Last Friday, culinary arts students from Jubilee-Lake View University Prep Prep competed in the SA HEAT High School Cupcake Battle at the University of Houston SA. Our very own Michelle Quinones (12th Grade) and Robin Kingsley (11th Grade) competed and took home a red and blue ribbon! post_text: 🧡💙 PreK(4) students at Jubilee-Destiny have been working hard to write sentences on their own!! They will have a new, state-of-the-art campus in August as our two Harlingen schools (Jubilee-Destiny and Jubilee-Harlingen) merge and serve PreK(4)-8th grade in the new facility. Registration is happening now! Learn more at https://jhar.jubileeacademies.org/.
